docs.abstract: If the market since mortgage costs recently fell is any indication, a similar move by the Fed may not have the impact it once did.
docs.snippet: If the market since mortgage costs recently fell is any indication, a similar move by the Fed may not have the impact it once did.
docs.lead_paragraph: Cheaper mortgages are usually a boon to the housing market. But this year, a sharp drop in mortgage rates hasn’t provided much of a lift, and that could bode poorly for the Federal Reserve’s efforts to shore up economic growth.

headline.main: Mortgage Rates Are Already Lower. They’re Not Helping Much.
headline.print_headline: Mortgages Are Cheap, But Having Little Effect

docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — For more than 300 years, the London Stock Exchange has been one of the world’s most enduring symbols of capitalism. But offering a market for trading shares is not enough for stock exchanges these days.

headline.main: London Stock Exchange to Buy Refinitiv, a Data Provider
headline.print_headline: London Exchange to Buy Data Provider Refinitiv

docs.abstract: Beijing’s leaders have increasingly focused on rekindling growth as the trade war drags on and negotiations prove difficult to control or predict.

docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — As China considers ways to retaliate against President Trump’s mounting tariffs, it has increasingly acknowledged that it must first address its main obstacle to punching back: its own slumping economy.

headline.main: China Wants to Hit Back at Trump. Its Own Economy Stands in the Way.

docs.abstract: The networks argue that the app, which streams broadcast television signals, should be shut down for copyright violations and for failing to compensate them.
docs.snippet: The networks argue that the app, which streams broadcast television signals, should be shut down for copyright violations and for failing to compensate them.
docs.lead_paragraph: America’s four major broadcast networks joined forces on Wednesday to sue a little-known nonprofit organization that streams television signals at no charge, arguing that the service should be shut down for copyright violations and for failing to compensate them.
